      "updated_at": "2021-03-03T15:26:49.598Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I lost my Vidiot power supply, and I can\u2019t find any documentation on the power connector size.<br>\nI know it takes a 5v DC 1.2A, but what size is the barrel / tip?<br>\nAlso what is the polarity?</p>",
      "like_count": 0,
      "reply_to_post_number": null,
      "is_wiki": false
    },
    {
      "id": 16198,
      "post_number": 2,
      "username": "SPIKE",
      "name": "SPIKE the Percussionist",
      "created_at": "2021-03-03T02:20:40.097Z",
      "updated_at": "2021-03-03T02:20:40.097Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Lars recommended to just use one of these.<br>\nthis is how i power mine\u2026</p><aside class=\"quote\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"1153\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://yyz1.discourse-cdn.com/flex031/user_avatar/community.lzxindustries.net/creatorlars/48/65_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <a href=\"https://community.lzxindustries.net/t/vidiot-power-supply-question/1153/3\">Vidiot Power Supply Question</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/helpdesk/21\"><span data-category-id=\"21\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category \" title=\"Questions and answers about issues with your equipment.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Helpdesk</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    You could power it from any 1.2Amp 5V source (like a phone charger) and a cable like this!  I\u2019m not sure if that helps.  Definitely don\u2019t power it by a voltage above 5V.\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
      "like_count": 0,
      "reply_to_post_number": null,
      "is_wiki": false
    },
    {
      "id": 16199,
      "post_number": 3,
      "username": "blobbob",
      "name": "bob",
      "created_at": "2021-03-03T02:40:53.519Z",
      "updated_at": "2021-03-03T02:44:22.984Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Thanks for the reply Spike.<br>\nSo\u2026 that usb cable looks to be 5.5mm OD /2.1mm ID, center is positive.<br>\nIs that same cable you use? I don\u2019t want to damage it with the wrong polarity.</p>",
      "like_count": 0,
      "reply_to_post_number": 2,
      "is_wiki": false
